notesStmt.note: Imperfect at the beginning and at the end.
Considerable water-damage at the top of the pages.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: A commentary on the Pentateuch in Arabic and Hebrew.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 33 34; written lines: 33 34; Ruled with a mastara. A number of marginal notes. Folio 8r contains a diagram with the names of patriarchs.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite semi-cursive script, unpunctuated, of the 16th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Commentary on the Pentateuch. Arabic & Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2386.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), an antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 23 July 1881, folio [140v].
